Title: Object: The Desolation of Egypt
Series: Etchings for the Art-Union of London by the Etching Club
Description: Plate 21: moonlit view in Egypt with a figure in the right foreground looking towards figures camping in the centre, by a tent on the right, shadow of Sphinx in the left background, the full moon above; scratched-letter state. 1857 Etching and drypoint, printed on chine collé
